Great idea.

14:33.917 --> 14:36.458
- ( brakes squeal )
- ( Hannah and Mimi-Rose
scream )

14:40.083 --> 14:42.291
Are you okay?

14:42.291 --> 14:44.000
I-- I think I'm--

14:44.000 --> 14:45.667
What's your name?

14:46.417 --> 14:48.500
- Mary.
- Mary, okay.

14:48.500 --> 14:50.959
Hey! Come here.
Can we get some help?

14:50.959 --> 14:53.375
- I'm so sorry, sir.
- His name's Adeem.

14:53.375 --> 14:55.917
Hannah:
Adeem, I'm so sorry
I asked you to turn.

14:55.917 --> 14:57.792
It's your fault.
It's her fault.

14:57.792 --> 14:58.959
Well, it's not my fault.

14:58.959 --> 15:00.417
Miss, are you
all right?

15:00.417 --> 15:03.208
Yes, yes,
I-- I'm all right.

15:03.208 --> 15:04.959
- What happened here?
- Our cab hit this woman.

15:04.959 --> 15:07.917
- Because of her.
- It was not because of me.
I wasn't driving.

15:07.917 --> 15:10.458
Ma'am, let's take the driver's
and lady's statements, and then
we'll get yours.

15:10.458 --> 15:12.208
Okay, but you're not
gonna pin this on me,

15:12.208 --> 15:13.959
and I know enough
to ask for a lawyer.

15:13.959 --> 15:15.291
Please wait
in the cab.

15:15.291 --> 15:18.250
This is totally bogus, okay?
Let's just hop in another cab.

15:18.250 --> 15:20.291
No, we can't abandon
Adeem and Mary.

15:20.291 --> 15:22.166
She's totally fine.
The police are here, okay?

15:22.166 --> 15:24.500
And I'm very hungry.
Let's at least wait
in the deli.

15:24.500 --> 15:27.834
- Fine.
- Okay, we're gonna
be in the deli,

15:27.834 --> 15:29.875
and, Adeem, I don't
want to upset you,

15:29.875 --> 15:32.000
but the meter
is still running.

15:37.750 --> 15:38.834
What smells?

15:38.834 --> 15:40.959
Oh, it's probably me.
I don't wear deodorant.

15:40.959 --> 15:42.000
I'm sorry.

15:42.000 --> 15:43.708
They have
coconut popsicles?

15:43.708 --> 15:45.959
Oh, this was
the last one.

15:45.959 --> 15:48.166
- Do you want mine?
- No, I'm good.

15:49.959 --> 15:52.000
Do you resent me
for dating Adam?

15:52.000 --> 15:55.208
What? Uh, no,
I don't resent you.

15:55.208 --> 15:57.834
I would never resent
another woman for that
and place blame on her.

15:57.834 --> 16:00.041
That is just not how I roll.
If I was gonna resent anyone,

16:00.041 --> 16:01.708
I would resent him.
I don't resent you.

16:01.708 --> 16:05.625
So, why are you mad at Adam,
if you were mad at Adam?

16:05.625 --> 16:07.708
I'm not mad at Adam,
but if I was,

16:07.708 --> 16:09.375
it'd probably be
because he's deceitful

16:09.375 --> 16:12.041
and because he didn't
tell me he was in love
with someone else,

16:12.041 --> 16:13.750
if that's even a word
you two are using.

16:13.750 --> 16:15.375
Not yet.

16:15.375 --> 16:18.000
And I would also
be angry at him for
being a coward.

16:18.000 --> 16:21.041
Because he is a coward,
and then he lashes out
like a maniac

16:21.041 --> 16:24.208
when you call him on anything
because he feels so guilty.

16:24.208 --> 16:26.708
Yep, that is Adam
in a nutshell.

16:36.792 --> 16:38.208
Can I use your bathroom?

16:38.208 --> 16:39.625
We don't have a bathroom.

16:39.625 --> 16:42.166
You do have a bathroom.
I just saw it.

16:42.166 --> 16:45.166
I saw what was
most definitely
a toilet, dude.

16:45.166 --> 16:47.208
It's for employees only.

16:47.208 --> 16:50.000
Okay, well, can you
just maybe bend those rules

16:50.000 --> 16:53.875
because I'm gonna buy
all this stuff and I really,
really, really have to pee.

16:53.875 --> 16:55.959
Sorry, it's the rules.

16:55.959 --> 16:58.083
Seriously?
You know what?
Fuck this.

16:58.083 --> 17:00.667
- We're fucking out of here.
- She has to pay for
the popsicle.

17:00.667 --> 17:03.458
- She's not paying
for the popsicle.
- This is a protest.

17:03.458 --> 17:04.959
Hey! You can't steal
the popsicle!

17:04.959 --> 17:06.625
- There's probably
a bathroom in there.
- Okay!

17:06.625 --> 17:10.458
Excuse me, we're gonna
be in here now!

17:12.125 --> 17:13.500
Go! Go!

17:13.500 --> 17:15.416
Mimi-Rose:
You were ready to beat
me down, weren't you?

17:15.416 --> 17:17.250
- ( toilet flushes )
- Woman: I know, I was
ready to fuss--

17:17.250 --> 17:19.416
like, what is she doing
getting in my underwear?

17:19.416 --> 17:21.040
- Like, is this
bitch crazy?
- I know.

17:21.040 --> 17:23.625
- Oh, Hannah, meet
my new friend Chezza.
- Hi.

17:23.625 --> 17:25.791
She caught me trying
to slip a note into
her dryer mid-spin

17:25.791 --> 17:27.500
and she ran over.
She was like, "What
are you doing?"

17:27.500 --> 17:30.083
( Chezza laughs )
But it turns out she had
written me a poem.

17:30.083 --> 17:33.125
- Yeah, I always wanted
to give a stranger a poem.
- ( laughs )

17:33.125 --> 17:34.959
I was in that bathroom
for less than two minutes.

17:34.959 --> 17:37.291
It's actually
a pretty great poem.
You want to hear it?

17:37.291 --> 17:39.625
- No, thank you.
- I just gotta read
the first line.

17:39.625 --> 17:41.000
It's so beautiful
and touching.

17:41.000 --> 17:43.375
You know what, Chezza?
I told you I'm not in
the mood for a poem,

17:43.375 --> 17:45.125
but thank you so much.

17:46.458 --> 17:47.458
Okay.

17:47.458 --> 17:49.625
Never a dull
fucking moment

17:49.625 --> 17:51.417
in this fucking city.

17:51.417 --> 17:54.792
Hannah, do you still
want Adam back?

17:54.792 --> 17:56.625
Fuck, no.

17:56.625 --> 17:59.834
Because if you did,
that's something that
we should talk about.

17:59.834 --> 18:02.333
We don't need
to talk about it.
I don't want him back.

18:02.333 --> 18:04.208
You told Jessa
that you wanted him back.

18:04.208 --> 18:07.125
Fucking Jessa.

18:07.125 --> 18:10.000
She is insane, and,
anyway, I change my mind.

18:10.000 --> 18:13.834
And even if I didn't change
my mind, it wouldn't matter
because he's with you now.

18:15.291 --> 18:17.667
Well, if you actually
did want him back,

18:17.667 --> 18:20.000
I might say,
"You can have him."

18:23.333 --> 18:27.000
You are laying out
a beaver trap,

18:27.000 --> 18:29.625
and I'm not gonna walk
into your beaver trap.

18:29.625 --> 18:31.792
Hannah, there's no trap.

18:31.792 --> 18:34.667
I think Adam
is an extraordinary person,

18:34.667 --> 18:35.834
but I've only known him
for a few months.

18:35.834 --> 18:37.959
If you feel like you two
should really be together,

18:37.959 --> 18:41.166
then I am not gonna
stand in the way of that.

18:41.166 --> 18:44.583
And I think that
that is something
that we need to discuss.

18:44.583 --> 18:49.458
Okay, and how would
we go about discussing this?

18:49.458 --> 18:52.750
Well, I wouldn't
just give him to you,

18:52.750 --> 18:56.542
but I feel like
we could figure
something out.

18:59.542 --> 19:03.041
I would subtly
distance myself
from him

19:03.041 --> 19:06.542
as you incrementally
worked your way back
into his life.

19:06.542 --> 19:09.542
Perhaps through
a joint creative project.

19:09.542 --> 19:13.667
Okay, you are insane,
and that's insane.

19:13.667 --> 19:16.583
Are you mad because
you gave up on art

19:16.583 --> 19:20.000
or because
you gave up on Adam
or is it both?

19:20.000 --> 19:22.875
I didn't give up
on Adam, okay?

19:22.875 --> 19:24.417
You stole him from me.

19:24.417 --> 19:27.000
You swooped in
under the cover of night

19:27.000 --> 19:29.708
and you took him
while I was away
at graduate school

19:29.708 --> 19:32.792
getting a graduate degree
in a form of art that
is actual art,

19:32.792 --> 19:35.583
unlike what you do,
which is not art.

19:35.583 --> 19:36.917
And you're not a genius.

19:36.917 --> 19:39.250
You're just tricking people
and confusing them,

19:39.250 --> 19:41.041
and I think you know
it's bullshit,

19:41.041 --> 19:43.417
and I think maybe
you should just admit it.

19:44.583 --> 19:46.708
I just-- I...

19:48.333 --> 19:51.792
I don't know.
I saw this photograph
from the 1940s.

19:51.792 --> 19:55.291
Well, that has fucking
nothing to do with what
we're talking about.

19:55.291 --> 19:59.375
It was a picture
of this little girl.

19:59.375 --> 20:01.583
She was Japanese,
five or six,

20:01.583 --> 20:04.542
and she was
standing next to a row
of American soldiers

20:04.542 --> 20:07.542
on her way
to an internment camp.

20:07.542 --> 20:11.041
And the caption,
it just said, "Girl."

20:11.041 --> 20:13.458
I thought, "'Girl'?

20:13.458 --> 20:16.250
Do any of these soldiers
even know this girl's name?"

20:16.250 --> 20:19.458
They probably didn't.
They were, like,
war criminals.

20:19.458 --> 20:24.792
But I think it's so easy
for us to get so wrapped up
in ourselves and our own lives

20:24.792 --> 20:27.458
that we just completely
lose our empathy.

20:27.458 --> 20:30.458
We don't want to get
to know other people.

20:30.458 --> 20:31.875
And I get it.

20:31.875 --> 20:34.125
It's easier
to not ask and not tell.

20:34.125 --> 20:37.625
It's easier not to know
someone's name.

20:40.583 --> 20:43.583
Well, it sounds like
you know what you're doing.

20:43.583 --> 20:48.792
And I'm sorry that
learning more about you
physically pains me.

20:48.792 --> 20:51.375
Why does it pain you?

20:51.375 --> 20:54.333
Oh, I don't know,
because of your book

20:54.333 --> 20:55.458
that's gonna be
a best seller,

20:55.458 --> 20:56.917
because of your
smash-hit lectures,

20:56.917 --> 20:59.000
because of your
little doll face.

20:59.000 --> 21:02.542
You know, it pains me
to find out shit
about you, too.

21:02.542 --> 21:04.041
Oh, save it, please.

21:04.041 --> 21:06.000
No, it's the truth,
Hannah.

21:06.000 --> 21:09.417
( laughs )
I know that you
hated my show.

21:09.417 --> 21:11.708
And the way
that you see me,

21:11.708 --> 21:14.667
I'm afraid
that that's the way
everyone sees me.

21:14.667 --> 21:18.667
I just want
to make something
that says something,

21:18.667 --> 21:21.542
and I don't even
know why anymore.

21:31.000 --> 21:33.208
You try because
you're an artist.

21:35.208 --> 21:38.250
And I couldn't do it,
so I quit.

21:38.250 --> 21:41.375
Now I'm gonna have
a boring life like
my mother's,

21:41.375 --> 21:43.542
be dissatisfied,
and I'm gonna be normal.

21:43.542 --> 21:46.291
Do you think
I want to be normal?

21:46.291 --> 21:49.875
I just wasn't talented enough,
and that is why I left Iowa.

21:55.875 --> 22:00.375
I think that we
should just go to the bar
and start drinking heavily.

22:01.708 --> 22:03.417
Let's get outta here.

22:04.667 --> 22:07.542
( music playing )

22:13.500 --> 22:15.250
Jessa:
Isn't Ace the coolest?

22:15.250 --> 22:16.667
Adam:
Fuck, no!

22:16.667 --> 22:18.375
He told me he was
gonna get M-R back.

22:18.375 --> 22:19.708
Said he was kidding,
but he wasn't.

22:19.708 --> 22:21.417
- He said that?
- Yeah.

22:21.417 --> 22:24.125
- He said he wanted her back?
- Yeah, he said she's playing
some kind of game

22:24.125 --> 22:25.500
and he always
gets her back.

22:25.500 --> 22:27.667
He's a fuckin' psycho.

22:27.667 --> 22:28.917
No.

22:28.917 --> 22:30.542
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

22:30.542 --> 22:32.500
He didn't
really say that.

22:32.500 --> 22:34.583
Yeah, why?

22:34.583 --> 22:37.375
This is the whole reason
why I set you up with her

22:37.375 --> 22:39.583
is so that
I could get Ace.

22:39.583 --> 22:41.708
He's not supposed
to still want her back.

22:41.708 --> 22:44.125
He's supposed
to love me now.

22:45.667 --> 22:47.750
Oh.

22:49.750 --> 22:52.375
I don't buy it.
He loves me.

22:52.375 --> 22:55.625
I'll be pregnant
with his twins by May.

22:59.333 --> 23:03.125
- Congratulations!
- Oh, thanks. Thank you.

23:03.959 --> 23:07.333
( squeals )
Oh, my God! Hi.

23:07.333 --> 23:10.125
You came.
Oh, you look so terrific.

23:10.125 --> 23:12.750
Woman:
Congratulations,
fancy lady.

23:12.750 --> 23:14.875
- Hey.
- Jesus fucking Christ.

23:14.875 --> 23:16.667
- Hey, sorry.
- Hey.

23:16.667 --> 23:19.333
You're probably
still mad at me
or whatever.

23:19.333 --> 23:21.375
No, I-- I am not trying
to make you unhappy.

23:21.375 --> 23:22.708
I don't want you
to be unhappy.

23:22.708 --> 23:23.875
I just want
everyone to be happy.

23:23.875 --> 23:26.083
I know, I feel
the exact same way.

23:26.083 --> 23:29.166
I just wanted to tell you
that I really like Mimi-Rose.

23:29.166 --> 23:30.458
Oh, okay.
All right, thank you.

23:30.458 --> 23:34.291
I'm not kidding, okay?
I think she's a really
special,

23:34.291 --> 23:36.083
unique, neat person,

23:36.083 --> 23:37.792
and my eyes have been
totally opened

23:37.792 --> 23:40.166
and I just-- I wanted
to let you know that

23:40.166 --> 23:42.166
and just say
congratulations,

23:42.166 --> 23:45.375
and I just wanted
to say that I...

23:45.375 --> 23:47.625
get it.

23:49.125 --> 23:51.291
So now I'll get out of here
before I make it bad again,

23:51.291 --> 23:54.458
but I just wanted
to say that and...

23:57.333 --> 23:59.500
Okay, thank you.

24:04.166 --> 24:05.875
Excuse me.

24:09.333 --> 24:12.750
Hey, um, can I get
a falafel sandwich
and a seltzer, please?

24:12.750 --> 24:14.125
What's your name?

24:14.125 --> 24:18.083
Oh, my name is Hannah.
What is your name?

24:18.083 --> 24:20.417
We'll call you
when it's ready.

